However, it is estimated that about 10 percent of cancers are caused by heredity.
Many of them remain completely unexplained.
The Canadian Cancer Society continues to make smoking a priority, despite the decline in the number of smokers.
Smoking is linked to 85 percent of lung cancer cases.
It is also a risk factor for several others.
It's a huge health hazard for people.
"Today, there are still 1.5 million smokers in Quebec", said spokesman André Beaulieu.
Encouraging fact: Ten years after quitting, the risk of dying from cancer drops by half.
Weight
Obesity and overweight also contribute to the onset of the disease, according to the CCS.
They would increase the risk of breast, colon and rectal, esophageal, pancreatic and uterine cancers.
"Research shows that regular lifelong physical activity protects against colon cancer", it adds.
Food
The agency also recommends limiting red meat consumption.
Too much of it increases the risk of colorectal cancer.
So are butcher shops, and they should be avoided.
The preservation of meat by smoking, drying or salting may lead to the formation of carcinogens.
"These can damage cells in the body and lead to cancer", it says.
The Vitamins
In recent years, several scientists have studied the links between vitamin supplements and cancer.
However, their research is not conclusive at present.
Studies on vitamin E are conflicting, according to the SCC.
While one study found a decreased risk of prostate cancer, another reported an increase.
